  "texts": [
    "The size of the vortex also affects the pressure drop; for inlet velocities up to 10 mm/s, the vortex for the 70°angle increases the pressure drop, but for the 90°angle, the pressure drop is slightly below the value for the 50°a ngle.",
    "The angle optimizer only found the local minimum at around 50°.",
    "The lower pressure drop for the 90°angle can be explained by the fact that the friction losses between the vortex and the main flow are lower than direct contact of the flow and the wall.",
    "In practice, however, these recirculation areas should be avoided because they can promote backflow in the nozzle or lead to material degradation in the vortex.",
    "This issue could be addressed in future work by modifying the objective function to consider vortices."
  ],
